! How a mapping profile works

A mapping profile is a small JSON document:

```
{
  "records": "{{books[*]}}",
  "tw-fields": {
    "title": "{{author}}: {{title}}",
    "tags":  "Book {{genre|split-csv}}"
  },
  "custom-fields": {
    "year": "{{year}}"
  }
}
```

* ''records'' points at the array of source records — one tiddler
  per element.
* ''tw-fields'' / ''custom-fields'' describe what each tiddler's
  fields look like.  `{{path}}` tokens resolve against the current
  record; `{{path|transform}}` pipes through a named transform.
* When ''records'' crosses multiple `[*]`s, bindings can use
  `{{../field}}` to reach the enclosing scope (see the Trip
  Itinerary and Music Library samples).

Open any sample profile via the Console's ''Edit'' button to see
the form-based editor.

! Installing the plugin in your own wiki

Drag the tiddler `$:/plugins/crosseye/json-convert` onto your own
wiki and save.  A {{$:/plugins/crosseye/json-convert/icon}} icon
appears in the page-controls toolbar.

